name: Codeforces Checking
description:
Given a lowercase Latin character (letter), check if it appears in the string

    
. Input The first line of the input contains an
integer 
    t
 (
    1 
    ≤ t 
    ≤ 26
) — the number of test cases. The
only line of each test case contains a character 
    c
 — a single lowercase
Latin character (letter). Output For each test case, output "YES" (without
quotes) if 
    c
 satisfies the condition, and "NO" (without quotes)
otherwise. You can output the answer in any case (for example, the strings
"yEs", "yes", "Yes" and "YES" will be recognized as a positive answer).
Example Input 10 a b c d e f g h i j Output NO NO YES YES YES YES NO NO NO NO
